19/12/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- UNMIK chief Soren Jessen-Petersen announced Friday (17 December) that more responsibility in the area of economic policy will be transferred to the interim Kosovo government. He also said discussions about the partial transfer of police and judicial duties will begin next year. The statement followed a meeting between Jessen-Petersen and Kosovo Prime Minister Ramush Haradinaj. 
In other news, three Kosovo TV stations have agreed to spend a total of 115,000 euros to train their reporters. The stations came under strong criticism for their coverage of the riots last March, with OSCE saying they may have contributed to the violence through biased and careless reporting. (AFP, KosovaLive, Tanjug - 17/12/04) 
